# Create a dendrogram using scipy and matplotlib
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
dendrogram = sch.dendrogram(linkage_matrix)
plt.title('Dendrogram')
plt.xlabel('Samples')
plt.ylabel('Distance')
plt.grid(False)

# Save the dendrogram as an image
image_path = 'dendrogram.png'
plt.savefig(image_path)
plt.close()

# Display the dendrogram image in the Streamlit app
st.image(image_path)
In this code, we use scipy.cluster.hierarchy.dendrogram to create a static dendrogram and then save it as an image using plt.savefig. Finally, we use st.image to display the dendrogram image within the Streamlit app.

This approach allows you to show the dendrogram in your Streamlit application without needing direct Plotly integration.





